solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    bool checkRecord(string s) {
        int absent = 0;
        int lateStreak = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == 'A') {
                absent++;
                if (absent >= 2) return false;
                lateStreak = 0;
            } else if (c == 'L') {
                lateStreak++;
                if (lateStreak >= 3) return false;
            } else {
                lateStreak = 0;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass through the string tracking two counters: total absences and current consecutive lates. Early exit on any violation keeps runtime minimal.

